Here's a complete example:

**XAML**
```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ItemsPage">

    <RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
                 Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">

        <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                        SelectionMode="Single"
                        SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem}"
                        SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
            <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
                <DataTemplate>
                    <Grid Padding="10" ColumnDefinitions="*,Auto">
                        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="16" />
                        <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Status}"
                               TextColor="Gray" />
                    </Grid>
                </DataTemplate>
            </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        </CollectionView>

    </RefreshView>
</ContentPage>
```

**ViewModel bindings explained:**

| Binding | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Items` | `ObservableCollection<T>` driving the list |
| `IsRefreshing` | `bool` — set `true` while loading, `false` when done; drives the spinner |
| `RefreshCommand` | `IAsyncRelayCommand` — calls your API, repopulates `Items`, then sets `IsRefreshing = false` |
| `SelectedItem` | `T?` — two-way bound to the tapped item |
| `ItemSelectedCommand` | Navigates to the detail page, then clears `SelectedItem` so the same row can be re-selected |

**ViewModel (CommunityToolkit.Mvvm)**
```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;

    [ObservableProperty] private bool _isRefreshing;
    [ObservableProperty] private ItemModel? _selectedItem;

    public ObservableCollection<ItemModel> Items { get; } = new();

    public IAsyncRelayCommand RefreshCommand { get; }
    public IRelayCommand ItemSelectedCommand { get; }

    public ItemsViewModel(IApiService api)
    {
        _api = api;
        RefreshCommand  = new AsyncRelayCommand(LoadDataAsync);
        ItemSelectedCommand = new RelayCommand(OnItemSelected);
    }

    private async Task LoadDataAsync()
    {
        IsRefreshing = true;
        var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
        Items.Clear();
        foreach (var item in data) Items.Add(item);
        IsRefreshing = false;
    }

    private void OnItemSelected()
    {
        if (SelectedItem is null) return;
        Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(DetailPage),
            new Dictionary<string, object> { ["Item"] = SelectedItem });
        SelectedItem = null;   // reset so re-tap works
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`RefreshView` wraps `CollectionView`** — it provides the pull-to-refresh gesture and spinner.
- **Clear `SelectedItem` after navigation** — otherwise tapping the same row again won't fire the command (selection hasn't "changed").
- **`SelectionChangedCommand`** fires automatically on selection change; no event handler needed in code-behind.
- Register the route in `AppShell.xaml.cs`: `Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(DetailPage), typeof(DetailPage));`
